{
  "text": "The South American palm weevil (SAPW), Rhynchophorus palmarum Linnaeus (Coleoptera: Curculionidae) is the most destructive insect of oil palm (Elaeis guineensis Jacquin) in the Americas. The SAPW also damages other palm tree species as Attalea maripa (Aubl. Mart.), Cocos nucifera (L.), Elaeis oleifera (Kunth), Jessenia bataua (Mart.), Mauritia flexuosa (L.F.), and Phoenix sylvestris (L.) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This insect",
